   GRANDS VINS DE BORDEAUX MIS EN BOUTEILLE AU CHÂTEAU.
   "Bordeaux by Despagne"

Despagne

   Located in Bordeaux, in the heart of the Entre-Deux-Mers appellation
   Vignobles Despagne has been perpetuating a family tradition of
   excellence for more than 200 years.

   The Despagne family business has been built around 5 châteaux (first
   mentioned in “Le Féret” in 1868). Thanks to an innovative approach to
   its terroirs and the vinification process it has become one of the most
   renowned names in winemaking.

   Today, the ‘Despagne’ product line offers a wide selection of colors
   and surprising flavors, appreciated and distributed worldwide.
   See the video
   About Brooklyn

OUR PROMISE

   As “winemakers” we are above all, and only for the space of a few
   vintages, tasked with caring for our terroir. It’s our responsibility
   to help it express itself in harmony with the surrounding environment.

   Wherever it may be, somewhere in London, Tokyo or Boston, if the person
   raising their glass is filled with pleasure and emotion then we will
   have attained our goal and our mission will be accomplished.
   About Brooklyn

   “Élu agriculteur de l’année pour une pratique de la viticulture
   respectant l’environnement.”

   “One of the most admirable operations in Bordeaux is that of the
   Despagne family, which produces extraordinary wines. They are
   visionaries and revolutionaries making wines that can compete with some
   of Bordeaux’s most renowed estates.”

Robert Parker

   Wine advocate n°152

   “1er vigneron français certifié ISO9001 et ISO14001.”

   “Entre Deux Mers superstar.”

Jancis Robinson

   “An attempt to produce great wine in some of Bordeaux’s least valued
   soils by unusual means, with astonishing commitment.”

Andrew Jefford

   Decanter

   “There is here a new kind of approach, a different technical path, a
   spirit of research which owes respect.”

François Mauss

   Grand Jury Européen

   “Girolate, it must be tasted to be believed.”

Robert Parker

